oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Park. James Park funeral card, 1894.
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: James Park funeral card, 1894. Died Dec. 18, 1894. Aged 72 years, 3 months, 19 days. He was identified as James B. Park, born 1821 or 1822 in Greene County, Tennessee, to parents Andrew and Eleanor Brown Park. In 1850 he married Margaret Armitage in Greene County, and they had five children, Mary, Martha, John, Charles M. and Emily Park. The funeral card was in an album of 32 unidentified 19th century photographs of individuals.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Funeral rites & ceremonies; Memorial rites & ceremonies;
